    [31mCARELABS PROVIDE FOLLOWING INSPECTION AND CERTIFICATION SERVICES NEEDED TO OBTAIN OFC[39m
    [31m[39m
    [31mBased on the Typical EHS Checklist for Operational Inspections following are the points that need to be fulfilled to obtain OFC.[39m
    [31m[39m
    [31mDefective electrical equipment/cables/apparatus etc shall be rectified prior to use. Warning tag system shall be in place until the equipment is rectified & ready for use.[39m
    [31mEarthing where necessary for any electrical equipment shall be done prior to undertake any work/repair/maintenance.[39m
    [31mThe isolators for machines should be identified with engraved label to indicate circuit number/source of supply.[39m
    [31mThe live electrical parts in the control panel should be shrouded.[39m
